<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1 is: A project shall not contain unreachable code.

</misra_rule>
<response format>
Provide your answer with these fields.
- is_rule_violated: whether the rule is violated or not (true/false),
- scenario: a specific violation scenario.
</response format>
<target_code>
Here is the code of OS_BinSemTimedWait_Impl:
```c
int32 OS_BinSemTimedWait_Impl(const OS_object_token_t *token, uint32 msecs)
{
    struct timespec ts;

    /*
     ** Compute an absolute time for the delay
     */
    OS_Posix_CompAbsDelayTime(msecs, &ts);

    return (OS_GenericBinSemTake_Impl(token, &ts));
}
```
</target_code>
<target_code>
Here is the code fragment that you need to analyze:
```c
return (OS_GenericBinSemTake_Impl(token, &ts));
```
Focus on the above code fragment and judge whether it violates the rule 2.1 or not.
</target_code>
scenario: No violation. The return statement is reachable (it is the last statement of the function and will be executed in normal control flow). There is no code after the return that could be unreachable. (A violation would occur if there were executable statements following this return, or if prior control flow made subsequent code impossible to reach.)
